    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-13T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-13T03:00:00-05:00" n="1090"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1090">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5123 Manchuria/8: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-13T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 13, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 13—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>816. The following telegram has been received from Mukden: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“15, December 10, 4 p.m. An income tax law has been promulgated,
                            effective January 1, and declared applicable to all residents of
                            Manchukuo.</p>
                        <p>Translation follows”.<note n="79" xml:id="d1090fn79">Not printed.</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>The Embassy will study the text of the law when received from Mukden.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department, repeated to Tokyo and Embassy, Hankow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
